# Home Stretch Plan — Gap Closure from old-js-app-fixed

## Summary

Detailed comparison of `fix/migration-full-plan` (SolidJS) against `origin/special/old-js-app-fixed` (Vanilla JS) revealed significant gaps in Transactions, Settings, Dashboard layout, Budget performance, Loan rendering, and general backend performance. This plan organizes all findings into prioritized, executable phases.

---

## Phase 1: Transactions Page — Full Rewrite of Missing Features (P0)

### 1.1 Fix Broken Filters
- **Category dropdown shows only already-selected categories** — `CategoryMultiSelect` filters to `props.selectedCategoryIds().includes(cat.id)`, making it impossible to select new categories. Fix the filter logic.
- **Tag filter receives empty data** — `tags` signal is hardcoded to `[]`. Load tags from `GET /tags` on mount.
- **Period presets are non-functional** — `_applyDatePreset` is dead code (prefixed `_`, `@ts-expect-error unused`). Wire date presets to FilterBar so clicking "This Month" actually filters.
- **No reconciliation toggle** — Add a reconciliation filter toggle with unreconciled count badge (old app had this).

### 1.2 Add Missing Table Columns & Features
- **Reconcile checkbox per row** — Add inline reconcile toggle to each transaction row.
- **Reconciled rows visually distinct** — Add CSS class for reconciled rows.
- **Category colored dot** — Add colored circle indicator next to category name.
- **Delete button per row** — Add inline delete with confirmation.
- **Counter-party column** — Add dedicated column instead of burying under description.
- **Sortable Category column** — Make category header clickable for sort.
- **Fix bulk action bar** — `BulkActionBar` exists but is never rendered. Wire it up.
- **Modal title** — Change to "Edit Transaction" when editing (currently always "Add").

### 1.3 Add Missing Summary & Pagination
- **Pagination info text** — Show "N transactions (page X/Y)".
- **Page size** — Change from 10 to 50 per page (match old app).
- **Bug: `totalItems` passed as raw `transactions().length`** — Should be filtered count.
- **Summary bar** — Add Total Amount and Transaction Count.

### 1.4 Fix Selection Bug
- `handleSelectionChange` calls `refreshTransactions()` on every checkbox toggle — fires full API reload. Remove this side-effect.

### 1.5 Add Recurring Transactions
- Old app had full CRUD for recurring transactions with populate-to-transactions. This is entirely missing. Implement:
  - Recurring transaction list section on Transactions page
  - Create/Edit/Delete recurring transactions
  - "Populate" button to generate a transaction from a recurring template

---

## Phase 2: Settings Page Fixes (P1)

### 2.1 Remove Duplicate Theme Toggle
- **SettingsDialog.tsx** has a theme toggle with LOCAL state only — it does not call `theme.setTheme()`. Either wire it to the core ThemeStore or remove it.
- Remove the `[theme, setTheme]` signal in `stores/index.ts` (lines 140-165) if unused, or consolidate.

### 2.2 Fix PDF Exports
- **Missing `export-monthly.html` and `export.html`** — These HTML templates are referenced by Puppeteer in the backend for PDF rendering but do NOT exist in the new repo. Copy them from the old app branch.
- **Add Annual PDF report option** — Backend supports `/api/reports/annual-pdf` but the UI has no button. Add "Annual Financial Report" to the Report Type dropdown.
- **Dynamic year population** — Year dropdowns are static (`currentYear - 2` to `currentYear + 2`). Should fetch from `/analytics/distinct-years` like the old app.
- **Year dropdown should support full year** — Old app could select "All Months" / full year, not just a single month. Add this option.

### 2.3 Export Format Selection
- Old app had a format dropdown for CSV/JSON/etc. New app hardcodes one format per button. Add format selection or match old app's single export section.

---

## Phase 3: Loan Calculator Bug Fix (P1)

### 3.1 Fix Infinite Scroll (Chart.js Responsive Feedback Loop)
- **Root cause**: `Chart.tsx` wrapper div has `height: '100%'` but no parent has explicit height. Chart.js ResizeObserver creates circular dependency — container height depends on canvas, canvas tries to fill container → unbounded growth.
- **Fix**: Change the wrapper div from `height: '100%'` to the explicit pixel value from `props.height` (e.g., `250px`).

### 3.2 Fix Amortization Table Overflow
- Basic amortization table renders ALL rows (up to 360 for a 30-year mortgage) with no max-height or overflow. Wrap in a scrollable container with `max-height: 500px; overflow-y: auto`.

### 3.3 Clean Up CSS Duplication
- `LoansPage.module.css` has 3 copies of the same class definitions (649 lines, ~40% is duplicates). Remove legacy duplicates.

---

## Phase 4: Budget Performance Fix (P1)

### 4.1 Fix Double-Fire Bug (CRITICAL)
- Both `onMount` AND `createEffect` call `loadData()` + `loadImprovements()` — page fires 8 API calls instead of 4.
- **Fix**: Remove `onMount` block, keep only `createEffect` (which auto-tracks `month()`).

### 4.2 Remove Redundant API Call
- `loadImprovements()` is called on every month change but returns 6-month data that is NOT month-specific. Move to `onMount` only, not in the effect.

### 4.3 Add Missing DB Index
- Create composite index: `CREATE INDEX idx_budgets_profile_start_date ON budgets(profile_id, start_date)` — all budget queries filter by both columns.

### 4.4 Add Request Debouncing
- Rapid month navigation triggers bursts of API calls with no AbortController. Add debounce (300ms) and cancel in-flight requests on month change.

---

## Phase 5: Dashboard Layout Parity (P2)

### 5.1 Restore 4-Column Stat Cards
- Old app: 4 cards (Income, Expense, Balance, Net Worth) in `grid-4`.
- New app: 3 cards (Net Worth, Income, Expense) in `repeat(3, 1fr)`.
- **Fix**: Add back Balance card, switch to `repeat(4, 1fr)` grid.

### 5.2 Fix Net Worth Data Source
- New app uses `metrics().balance` (sum of all account balances) — this is NOT net worth.
- Old app used a dedicated `/dashboard/net-worth` endpoint that calculated assets minus liabilities.
- **Fix**: Either call the proper endpoint or calculate correctly.

### 5.3 Change Month-over-Month Format
- Old app showed percentage changes (`▲ 5.3%`), new app shows raw currency amounts (`↑ 523.45`).
- **Fix**: Switch to percentage-based comparison.

### 5.4 Restore 12-Month Bar Chart
- Old app: 12-month Income vs Expense bar chart showing trends over time.
- New app: Single-period comparison with 3 bars (Income, Expense, Net).
- **Fix**: Query 12 months of data and render stacked monthly bars.

### 5.5 Chart Grid Layout
- Old app: Equal `1fr 1fr` chart grids.
- New app: Uneven `2fr 1fr` grids.
- **Fix**: Match old app's even split.

---

## Phase 6: Backend Performance (P2)

### 6.1 Fix Session Store (HIGH impact)
- `resave: true` forces a SQLite write on EVERY request, even when session is unchanged.
- `saveUninitialized: true` creates sessions for unauthenticated users.
- **Fix**: Set both to `false`. This alone should significantly reduce DB I/O.

### 6.2 Add Composite Transaction Index
- `CREATE INDEX idx_transactions_profile_date ON transactions(profile_id, date)` — the most common query pattern across the entire app uses both columns.

### 6.3 Remove Debug console.log Statements
- 6 `console.log` calls in category mappings route handlers. Remove them.

### 6.4 Fix Duplicate Route Registration
- `GET /api/categories/mappings` is registered twice (lines 1079 and 1258). Remove the duplicate.

### 6.5 Parallelize Dashboard Queries
- `/api/dashboard` runs 6 queries sequentially. At least 4 of them are independent and can be parallelized with `Promise.all`.

### 6.6 Fix Sync File I/O in Error Logger
- `logError` uses `fs.readFileSync` + `fs.writeFileSync` — blocking the event loop. Convert to async `fs.promises`.

---

## Phase 7: Emoji & CSS Cleanup (P3)

### 7.1 Remaining Emoji Scan
- Run a comprehensive emoji scan across all `.tsx` files, replace any remaining emojis with SVG icons or clean text per the old app's classy style.

### 7.2 CSS Parity
- Review all page layouts against old app `base.css` and `components.css` — match font sizes, spacing, card padding, and grid layouts exactly.

---

## Phase 8: Verification

- `npm run build` — zero errors
- `npm run lint` — clean
- Visual comparison against old app screenshots
- Test: Transactions page loads data, filters work, sorting works
- Test: Settings PDF exports generate correctly
- Test: Loan calculator charts render without infinite scroll
- Test: Budget page loads without double API calls
- Test: Dashboard shows 4 stat cards with correct data
- Git commit + push per phase

